- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as polar codes are a topic in information theory and the paper focuses on encoding and decoding of these codes.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of parallel decoders and encoders, which can be seen as control systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper proposes new algorithms for encoding and decoding polar codes.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possibility as the paper discusses the implementation of parallel decoders and encoders, which can be seen as hardware architecture.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the trade-off between decoding latency and computational complexity.
